rComments: Dr K. is one of the best profs at the university of Ottawa! She cares about the students wellbeing and will make sure to explain a concept several different ways if needed. Her lectures were always something I looked forward to... she makes a 3-hour lecture go by in no time! I wish she taught more classes so I could enroll in those as well!

During my almost six years of studying psychology at 3 different universities, this class has been one of my favourites for sure! Dr Kennedy has lots of hands-on experience in the field she shares in her lectures. It inspired me to pursue a career in Forensic Psychology. She encourages discussions and is very approachable even after class.

Professor Kennedey is amazing. The way she communicates herself is so clear and she makes lectures so interesting that the usual 3 hours didn't feel long. One midterm and final 50/50, MC, short answers and very fair. There's a lot of material but it's sooo interesting. This is one class I'm sad is ending. The textbook readings are essential.

Absolutely best prof! She really knows and loves the material which makes her teaching engaging. She cares about her students and encourages open discussions. I really recommend taking this class with her, she will make you want to come to school. The exams are 40% and 60% and are long, but they are easy if you come to class and read the book.

Knowledgeable and well respected prof! Looks happy to be lecturing, is very kind to her students and ensures the material is clear to everyone. Incorporates videos, guest lectures and power points in her course. One midterm and one final. Very specific, touching on each chapter of the textbook. Make sure to reach the textbook chapters.

Absolutely fantastic professor! Her real-life examples were extremely helpful in illustrating the readings and her lecturing style completely captivated us during an evening grad-level course. Assessment style was fair and there was no surprise with the grading schema. Encouraged open questions & discussion - extremely valuable! HIGHLY recommend!!

One of the best psych profs I've had at uOtttawa. Engaging and never made the 7-10 class boring. Gives you so many real-life examples from her career to help you understand concepts. Such an interesting course worth the wait on the waiting list. Exams are fair and reflect what was discussed in class. 60% final is a bummer but study and go to class.
Does not give students any grades until the course ends. Gives minimal feedback. Does not answer e-mail. Learned very little in this class. Very poor quality. Very repetitive in her lectures.

One of the best profs I've had so far! She is really engaging, cares about her students and is passionate about the subject. Has so many interesting stories to share and has a great sense of humour. She made lectures fun. My only complaint is that there is only one midterm (40%) and a final (60%). Definitely recommend taking a course with her.

A hell of a teacher! One of my favourites, hands down. She's engaging and interesting. There's a midterm and a final, and they're both precise and to the point. Material is awesome and a few guest speakers who are actually fun to listen to. Show up to class, do your readings and you'll pass with flying colours. Even brought candy on Halloween!!

Really good prof. Lectures are interesting, and there are several guest speakers that come in. We watched lots of videos in class too. There's only a midterm and an exam (50%/50%). I really enjoyed this class!
Really interesting and sweet teacher.

Found the course a little dry at first (too much law, not enough psych) but the second half was awesome. Prof Kennedy is a super nice person. Exams are totally reasonable. If you study there's no reason you shouldn't get an A. Interesting guest lectures and videos. Only criticism is the heavy textbook use.. sometimes makes the lectures boring.

Midterm and final are worth 50% each and consist of mp and short answer. She does go over what will be on the exams, but it's pretty much everything. Attendance is mandatory, and there's a sign in sheet. She knows her stuff and clearly conveys it. All in all a good class and teacher.
Very intereting if you're into criminals and all that jazz.  Two tests: midterm - 50%, final - 50%. if you're willing to do the reading and go to class, DO IT!
Awesome passionate prof
Great prof! By far my favorite class. Dr. Kennedy is very passionate and engaging!

Very well organized and interesting prof. Class material is ok, some good sections. Need to read chapters ahead of class to do well. Open to talk to students after class and keeps class interested by giving real life examples and engaging conversations in class.
Comes highly recommended to stimulate your mind!  Great prof! Will need to learn many concepts on your own though, otherwise great course!!!!

Took her for Forensic Psychology, awesome topic but the 3 hour lectures on a Friday night kind of killed it! Overall, passionate prof, learned alot! Make sure you read the book as her slides are just a guideline.

Amazing prof. Passionate about the subject and her students. It's a joy to hear her talk, and she knows so much. Exams are fair, you do have to keep up with the readings though. I wish she taught more than just the one course!
i look forward to her class every week. amazing prof. so intelligent and knowledgable .. great class
